post1: Long awaited catch up with life long friends!  Why has it taken so long? It was so good to catch up with everybody.  It has been so great seeing how we have all changed and grown both physically and spiritually.  Let me know who is up for making this an annual event? Please let me know.  I am happy to organise it.  Feeling blessed.  Cheers everyone!
post2:
Happy birthday to the best and most wonderful husband I could ever ask for xx  Thank you for everything you do. Thank you for being an awesome dad to our two children. Enjoy your day and look forward the birthday celebrations tonight.  Enjoy your gifts. 
 You  so deserve them.  Love as always.

post1:
Day 1s! 
We finally met up after so long - It was so lovely to catch up with all of you. It has been way too long since we last saw each other, and it really good to hear that you're all doing well. So much has changed since we used to see each other daily, but somehow it feels like no time has passed when we got back togehter
Let me know when you're all back in town - we can hang out again.
post2:
Happy birthday!!
I hope you had an amazing day with friends and family - and thank you for letting me share it with you. I'm so proud of all you've achieved this past year. It has been full of many great times and I'm sure the next year will be full of lots of new opportunities. I look forward to spending the next year with you 
See you later today!

post1: Tonight I discovered that if you hang out with a bunch of people who you were friends with in school but haven't seen for approximately.... 30 mumble years...., you will spend a LOT of the time feeling just as awkward as you did when you were a teenager, a LOT of the time comparing your current need for reading glasses and/or perimenopausal symptoms, and a LOT of the time feeling as though you've blocked out half your memories.
